notes:
The "Mutations EP" tracks are adaptations of earlier tracks off the debut album "293107" (2006) and demos that later became the tracks on the second album "188433" (2009).

Track "Caos Calmo" is a reworked "The Nothing Changes" from "293107" (2006);
Track "München" is a reworked "Lobby" from "293107" (2006);
Track "Serpents" is a reworked "Pearls For Swine" from "293107" (2006);
Track "Twisted Horizons" contains some elements from "Parallel Corners" from "293107" (2006);
Track "Shadows" later reworked in "Embers" on "188433" (2009) and contains melody from "Senki Dala" by Venetian Snares appeared on "3567" (2005) album (or "Senki Dala & Öngyilkos Vasárnap (Bong-Ra Remix)" from "110544" (2006) by Venetian Snares vs Bong-Ra);
Track "Symmetry Of 6's" contains some elements of "Solomon's Curse" from "293107" (2006);
Track "Horns Of King David" contains some elements of "Guernican Perspectives" from "293107" (2006);
Track "Avian Lung" later reworked to "Seneca" on "188433" (2009).
